# Discord Chat Analysis for ðŸ’¬-coders

## 1. Summary:
The chat primarily revolves around ElizaOS development issues and WhatsApp integration. Several users experienced problems with the ElizaOS CLI, particularly version conflicts between 1.4.3 and 1.5.10. A recurring issue involves port conflicts during development mode, where `elizaos dev` creates a loop of port reassignments. Users troubleshooted package manager conflicts between npm and bun installations. There was also discussion about WhatsApp integration with ElizaOS for AI auto-reply functionality, with multiple developers offering assistance. Other topics included security concerns about compromised npm packages and Solana's new podcast about crypto and AI called x402. One user mentioned implementing Solana USDC payments with a FastAPI backend for AI integration.

# Discord Chat Analysis for "core-devs" Channel

## 1. Summary:
The core-devs channel discussion focused on several technical topics. Odilitime identified duplicate entries in the .gitignore file that needed cleanup and mentioned getting a project-starter working. Stan shared a GitHub Actions workflow issue with Claude-review showing an invalid API key error, which sayonara offered to fix. Stan also requested review for PR #5864, mentioning defined next steps from tickets. Agent Joshua discussed UX feedback on an Eliza agent, noting a minute-long response time, and shared plans to create an agent that registers itself onchain with a generated wallet using ERC-8004 contracts. The team discussed ERC-8004 implementation, with Agent Joshua confirming deployment experience and work with Chaos Chain using Spore for onchain collaboration. Sam-developer provided an update on the elizaos cloud platform and plugin, demonstrating a working end-to-end flow where users can use the ElizaOS Cloud API key directly in the CLI without needing separate provider keys. Jin shared information about tldraw SDK 4.0, suggesting it could give Eliza an edge over other AI apps and noting that canvas interfaces represent the next evolution beyond chat interfaces.

## 2. FAQ:
Q: Has anyone deployed 8004 contracts? (asked by sayonara) A: I've done it and we've been working with them to make TEE validation more defined. We also did registered agents with Chaos Chain using Spore to collaborate on proposals, vote and execute proposals onchain during ETHDenver. (answered by Agent Joshua â‚± | TEE)
